      "heading": "Contacting businesses directly during the solicitation period",
      "heading_path": [
        "Contacting businesses directly during the solicitation period"
      ],
      "text": "Sometimes commodity or market knowledge may lead a buyer to conclude that businesses supplying a good or service will not see or respond to a solicitation of offers if it appears only on the Government Electronic Tendering Service (GETS). To stimulate effective competition and seek best value for Canadian taxpayers, you may notify all such known businesses that the solicitation opportunity has been posted. This communication must only occur after the Notice of Proposed Procurement (NPP) has been posted on the GETS . You should contact businesses as soon as possible afterwards so that they do not lose time.",
